  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0d85\u0d9f\u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dc0\u0dda\u0dc2\u0dab \u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba \u0db1\u0dc0 \u0da1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd6\u0db4 \u0d91\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China's Mars probe sends back new photos",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "China's Mars rover Tianwen-1 orbiter has sent back high-resolution images of the Red Planet's moon Phobos to mark the two-year anniversary of its mission.",
        "China launched the Tianwen-1 mission on July 23, 2020, sending the orbiter, lander and rover to the Red Planet. The orbiter entered Mars orbit in February 2021 and the lander and rover touched down on Mars and began operations in May 2021.",
        "Mars has two small natural moons, Phobos and Deimos. Phobos is the larger of the two moons.",
        "It is a small, irregularly shaped object with a mean radius of 11 km that orbits in a circular orbit about 6,000 km from the surface of Mars. It completes one orbit in 7 hours 39 minutes."
      ],
